<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Beignets | Taste The Movies</title>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Taste The Movies</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <div>
        <img src="images/placeholder.png" alt="Beignets from the movie The Princess and the Frog" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Classic New Orleans Beignets</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
        <p>A real Southern staple, these fluffy, golden-fried beignets are dusted with powdered sugar and made famous in <em>The Princess and the Frog</em>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 tsp active dry yeast</li>
          <li>¾ cup warm water</li>
          <li>¼ cup sugar</li>
          <li>1 egg</li>
          <li>½ cup milk</li>
          <li>3½ cups flour</li>
          <li>¼ cup butter, melted</li>
          <li>Oil for frying</li>
          <li>Powdered sugar</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Activate yeast in warm water with sugar and let sit for a few minutes.</li>
          <li>Add milk, egg, melted butter, and flour to the yeast mixture. Knead until smooth.</li>
          <li>Let the dough rise for 1-2 hours until it doubles in size.</li>
          <li>Roll dough to ½" thickness and cut into squares or rectangles.</li>
          <li>Heat oil in a deep fryer or large pot, and fry beignets until golden brown.</li>
          <li>Dust with powdered sugar and serve warm.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>

